
Overview of verb sharpen

The verb sharpen has 8 senses (first 4 from tagged texts)
                                        
1. (1) sharpen -- (make sharp or sharper; "sharpen the knives")
2. (1) sharpen -- (make crisp or more crisp and precise; "We had to sharpen our arguments")
3. (1) sharpen -- (become sharp or sharper; "The debate sharpened")
4. (1) focus, focalize, focalise, sharpen -- (put (an image) into focus; "Please focus the image; we cannot enjoy the movie")
5. sharpen -- (make (images or sounds) sharp or sharper)
6. sharpen -- (raise the pitch of (musical notes))
7. sharpen, taper, point -- (give a point to; "The candles are tapered")
8. sharpen, heighten -- (make (one's senses) more acute; "This drug will sharpen your vision")
